        <!-- Mint Slime Recipe-->
        <h2 class="mslime" id="mint-slime">Mint Slime</h2>
        
        <!--Image-->
        <!--<img src=" width="190" alt="gooey slime dripping from hands">-->
   
        <!--Time and Servings-->
        <ul class="mslime-content">
            <li>Time: 5 mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 2</li>
        </ul>
       
        <!-- Table of Ingredients and Quantity-->
        <table class="mslime-content">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th class="mslime">Ingredients and Materials</th>
                    <th class="mslime">Quantity</th>
                </tr>
              
               <!-- Bowl -->
                <tr>
                <td>bowl</td>
                <td>medium to big </td>
                </tr>
             
               <!-- Mixer -->
                <tr>
                    <td>wooden spoon</td>
                    <td>medium size</td>
                </tr>
               
               <!--Packaging-->
                <tr>
                <td>small container</td>
                <td>2</td>
                </tr>
              
               <!-- Glue -->
                <tr><td>Elmer's liquid glue</td>
                    <td>half of the medium sized bottles</td>
                </tr>
               
               <!-- Smoothness -->
                <tr>
                    <td>hair conditioner</td>
                    <td>one pump</td>
                </tr>
                
                <!-- Activator -->
                <tr>
                    <td>liquid tide detergent</td>
                    <td>2 caps</td>
                </tr>
                
                <!-- Colour -->
                <tr>
                <td>green food colouring</td>
                <td>1 drop</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <!-- Instructions -->
        <h3 class= "mslime">Instructions</h3>
              <p class="mslime-content"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Pour the glue and hair conditioner into the bowl
</p>          
              <p class="mslime-content"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix it until its smooth</p>
             
              <p class= "mslime-content"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Mix in the food colouring</p>
            
              <p class="mslime-content"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Slowly turn in the tide until you see it sticking a little, but not too little</p>
              
              <p class="mslime-content"><strong>Step 5:</strong> (A little messy) Pick up the slime and knead it until it's together</p>
            
              <p class="mslime-content"><strong>Step 6:</strong> If it's too strong, add a but more glue. if it's too runny, add a bit more tide</p>

<p class="mslime-content">Now you know how to make your very own mint slime. Play with a friend!</p>
        
        <!--Kit Kat Shake recipe-->
        <h2 class="kks-content" id="kit-kat-shake">Kit Kat Shake</h2>
       
        <!--Image-->
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/chocolates.png" width="190" alt= "box of chocolates">
        <!--Time and Servings-->
        <ul class="kks">
            <li> Time: 7 mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 2 grande starbucks cups</li>
       </ul>
       
       <!-- Table -->
       <table class="kks">
           <thead>
               <tr>
                   <th class="kks-content">Ingredients and Materials</th>
                   <th class="kks-content">Quantity</th>
               </tr>
               
               <tr>
                   <td>blender</td>
                   <td>one</td>
               </tr>
               
               <!--Chocolate Kit Kat shaving-->
               <tr>
                   <td>kit kat shavings</td>
                   <td>3 bricks</td>
               </tr>
              
               <!--Milk-->
               <tr>
                    <td>milk</td>
                    <td>1 & 1/2 grande starbucks cups</td>
               </tr>
               
               <!--Ice Cream-->
               <tr>
                    <td>French vanilla ice cream</td>
                    <td>2 scoops</td>
               </tr>
               
           </thead>
       </table>
        
        <!--Instructions-->
       <h3 class="kks-content">Instructions</h3>
       
       <p class="kks">Put all the ingredients in the blender and blend. <br>If you have a blender with settings like: dice, milkshake...put it on milkshake. <br>If you have a blender with settings 1-5, put it on 3 or 4.<br>Ultimately, you want it to blend at a medium pace. </p>
       <p class="kks">Blend it for a while and mix. Repeat until your satisfied with the texture, or someone gets annoyed by the sound.</p>
       <p class="kks">Finally, pour in a cup(s) and share with friends/family or store in fridge.</p>
   
    <!--Mug Cake Recipe-->
    <h2 class="mcake-content" id="mug-cake">Mug Cake</h2>
    
    <!--Image-->
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/Tassenkuchen_.jpg" width="190" alt="picture of mugcake">
    
    <!--Time and Servings-->
    <ul class="mcake">
        <li>Time: 10-15 mins</li>
        <li>Serves: 1</li>
    </ul>
    
    <!--Table-->
    <table class="mcake">
        <tr>
    
    <!--Ingredients and Materials-->
            <th class="mcake-content">Ingredients and Materials </th>
            <th class="mcake-content">Quantity</th>
            
            <!--Microwave-->
            <tr>
                <td>microwave</td>
                <td>----</td>
            </tr>
            
            <!--Large mug-->
            <tr>
                <td>mug</td>
                <td>large</td>
            </tr>
            
            <!--Tablespoon-->
            <tr>
                <td>tablespoon</td>
                <td>1-3</td>
            </tr>
            
            <!--Flour-->
            <tr>
                <td>pancake mix</td>
                <td>4 tablespoons</td>
            </tr>
            
            <!--Milk-->
            <tr>
                <td>milk</td>
                <td>1 tablespoons</td>
            </tr>
            
            <!--Ice Cream-->
            <tr>
                <td>ice cream of your   choice</td>
                <td>2 tablespoons</td>
                
            <!--Vanilla Extract-->
            <tr>
                <td>vanilla extract</td>
                <td>2 drops</td>
            </tr>
            </tr>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <!--Instructions-->
    <h3 class="mcake-content">Instructions</h3>

    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 1:</strong> Scoop the pancake mix into the mug</p>
   
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 2:</strong> Add the milk and mix</p>
    
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 3:</strong> Scoop the ice cream in and mix</p>
    
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 4:</strong> Put the vanilla extract in the mug and turn again</p>
    
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 5:</strong> Pop your mugcake mix into the microwave for 1 minute to start.</p>
    
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 6:</strong> Check if it's ready by sticking a skewer stick in the middle. If it comes up clean, let cool. If not, microwave for 30 secs.</p>
   
    <p class="mcake"
><strong>Step 7:</strong> Repeat step 6</p>
   
    <p class="mcake"
>Enjoy your mugcake, and share this recipe with friends!</p>
    
